Class MultiPartGetMessage

    • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.Message

    Serializable

    public class MultiPartGetMessage
extends GetMessage
implements Serializable
    Represents an OutMessage with the method type as GET and that will be sent to the server to download a file from it.
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:

    • Constructor Detail

      • MultiPartGetMessage

        public MultiPartGetMessage(Resource resourcePath,
                   String fullFilePath)
        Builds MultiPartGetMessage instance using the resource path and the file path where the downloaded content should be saved
        Parameters:
        resourcePath - the Resource path where the REST request needs to be sent to
        fullFilePath - the entire file path (till the name of the file) where the byte data of the response will be saved. This is useful for cases where for a GetMessage call we expect application/octet-stream data from the server. Basically for cases where image/video/pdf document/any other type needs to be downloaded from the server
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the file path passed is null or empty string

      • executeServerCall

        public void executeServerCall(HttpURLConnection connection)
                       throws IOException,
                              CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException
        Description copied from class: OutMessage
        The logic to make a request to the server and getting the response/headers back from the server should be done in this method. The implementation would depend upon the method type using which the request has to be made to the server.
        Note: Different subclass implementations can throw the below exceptions
        Overrides:
        executeServerCall in class GetMessage
        Parameters:
        connection - the HttpURLConnection connection object using which the call needs to be made to the server
        Throws:
        IOException - there was an i/o error at the time of connecting with the server or some error at the time of reading the input data
        CreateMultipartGetMsgFileException - if there is an error in creating the file for the artifact that was downloaded in the MultiPartGetMessage instance
